<br>
I have decent resist gear, all my BD stuff, and can wear about half of it and still stay over 200. When I need max resists I can put all of it on and drop down to around 180. Since some of that gear has +mana on it too I don't miss the mana I would have gained from the extra 20 Int. <br>
<br>
Point: Dropping below 200 is not the end of the world. <br>
<br>
I can easily buff all my resists (well ok not PR or DR) over or near 150 and still maintain a very large mana pool. I can do that while having the lowest base INT of any Wizard I have ever seen in Norrath.  <p><center><img width="189"height="161"src="http://verbalsabre.50megs.com/images/nice.jpg"><font size="-1"><p><i><b><a href="http://www.phoenixhorizon.com">Phoenix Horizon</a><br>54 Channeler<br><a href="http://verbalsabre.50megs.com">Sabre</b></i></a></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uorvie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orvie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/30/01 1:32:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Humans and 200 INT</span><hr size=1> Human wizard here also...and wouldn't trade it for anything.<br>
